# Brief Analysis Workflow (Smart Executor)

## Core Function
Apply the human MD instructions to locate the brief, summarize requirements, derive stack/compliance, and optionally emit PLAN artifacts.

## `[MUST]` - Context & Inputs
- Prefer `docs/briefs/*/brief.md` if present; else require explicit path.
- Capture `{{BRIEF_PATH}}` if provided.

## `[MUST]` - Apply MD
Apply instructions from: `/workspace/docs/workflows/01_BRIEF_ANALYSIS.md`
- Validate acceptance per step; capture evidence of files created.

## `[SHOULD]` - Stack/Compliance Inference
- Mirror `brief_parser` heuristics to propose FE/BE/DB/Auth/Deploy and compliance options.

## Evidence & Acceptance
- Evidence: summary text + created artifacts (PLAN.md, *.tasks.json)
- Acceptance: requirements summary present; questions captured; artifacts (if requested) generated

## Failure Handling
- Missing brief path → prompt to specify or create one
- Conflicting signals → record as open questions